    "title": "Satanás",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "satanás",
    "language": "por",
    "content": "<p>O livro de Jó menciona &quot;o Satanás&quot; como parte da corte celestial (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:6\">Jó 1.6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:1\">2.1</a>). (A corte celestial é uma reunião no céu onde Deus se encontra com seus anjos.) Em hebraico, <em>Satanás</em> significa um adversário ou Acusador no tribunal (veja <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:1-Job2:13\">Jó 1–2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:1\">Zc 3.1</a>). Deus às vezes usa anjos como adversários para julgamento justo e para se opor aos malfeitores (por exemplo, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:22\">Nm 22.22</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:32\">32</a>, onde <em>Satanás</em> é frequentemente traduzido como &quot;opor-se&quot;; veja também <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19-1Kgs22:23\">1Rs 22.19–23</a>).</p><p>O Antigo Testamento sugere que o Acusador tem uma natureza demoníaca. Mas foi no período entre o Antigo e o Novo Testamento que Satanás passou a ser associado à serpente no Éden (veja <em>Sabedoria de Salomão</em> 2.24). O Novo Testamento chama o principal demônio de &quot;Satanás&quot; (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">Ap 20.2</a>). O Novo Testamento usa outros nomes como:</p><ul><li><p>O diabo (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">Mt 4.1–11</a>)</p></li><li><p>O tentador (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:5\">1Ts 3.5</a>)</p></li><li><p>Beelzebul, o príncipe dos Demônios (veja notas em <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24\">Mt 12.24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15\">Lc 11.15</a>)</p></li><li><p>O maligno (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:19\">Mt 13.19</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:38\">38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:13-1John2:14\">1Jo 2.13–14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">3.12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:18\">5.18</a>)</p></li><li><p>Belial (veja a nota em <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:15\">2Co 6.15</a>)</p></li><li><p>O enganador (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">Ap 12.9</a>)</p></li><li><p>Um enorme dragão vermelho com sete cabeças (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3\">Ap 12.3</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">9</a>)</p></li><li><p>Antiga serpente (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">Ap 20.2</a>)</p></li><li><p>Um assassino e o pai da mentira (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">Jo 8.44</a>)</p></li></ul><p>Satanás fez muitas coisas más contra Deus e as pessoas. Ele fez Davi contar seu exército quando não deveria ter feito (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:1\">1Cr 21.1</a>; compare <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:1\">2Sm 24.1</a>). Satanás tentou induzir Jesus a cometer erros e mais tarde ajudou Judas a trair Jesus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">Mc 1.12–13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:27\">Jo 13.27</a>). Ele queria testar a fé de Pedro como testou Jó (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">Lc 22.31</a>). Ele prendeu pessoas no pecado (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">At 26.17–18</a>). Ele usou mentiras para se opor ao povo de Deus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1Co 7.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:14\">2Co 11.14</a>). No final, Deus derrotará e aprisionará Satanás, superando o adversário do povo de Deus (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">Ap 12.9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">20.2</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">10</a>).</p><p><u>Passagens para estudo complementar</u></p><p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:22\">Números 22.22</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:32\">32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:1\">1 Crônicas 21.1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:6-Job2:7\">Jó 1.6–2.7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:1-Zech3:4\">Zc 3.1–4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:10\">Mateus 4.1–10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:24\">12.24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:19\">13.19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:38-Matt13:39\">38–39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">16.23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">Marcos 1.13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:15\">4.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:6\">Lucas 4.6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17-Luke10:20\">10.17–20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:15\">11.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3\">22.3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">João 8.44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">12.31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:2\">13.2</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:27\">27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:11\">16.11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:9-Acts13:10\">Atos 13.9–10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">26.17–18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">Romanos 16.20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1 Coríntios 7.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:10-2Cor2:11\">2 Coríntios 2.10–11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">4.4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:15\">6.15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:13-2Cor11:15\">11.13–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:5\">1 Tessalonicenses 3.5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:2-2Thess2:12\">2 Tessalonicenses 2.2–12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">Hebreus 2.14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:7\">Tiago 4.7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8\">1 Pedro 5.8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:13-1John2:14\">1 João 2.13–14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">3.12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:18\">5.18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3\">Apocalipse 12.3</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">20.2</a>,<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">10</a></p>",
